{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":954,"text":"My colleagues and I are fascinated\nby the science of moving dots."},{"time":4927,"text":"So what are these dots?"},{"time":6101,"text":"Well, it's all of us."},{"time":7412,"text":"And we're moving in our homes,\nin our offices, as we shop and travel"},{"time":12521,"text":"throughout our cities\nand around the world."},{"time":14958,"text":"And wouldn't it be great\nif we could understand all this movement?"},{"time":18918,"text":"If we could find patterns and meaning\nand insight in it."},{"time":22259,"text":"And luckily for us, we live in a time"},{"time":24068,"text":"where we're incredibly good\nat capturing information about ourselves."},{"time":28807,"text":"So whether it's through\nsensors or videos, or apps,"},{"time":32494,"text":"we can track our movement\nwith incredibly fine detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36092,"text":"So it turns out one of the places\nwhere we have the best data about movement"},{"time":41148,"text":"is sports."},{"time":42682,"text":"So whether it's basketball or baseball,\nor football or the other football,"},{"time":48039,"text":"we're instrumenting our stadiums\nand our players to track their movements"},{"time":52465,"text":"every fraction of a second."},{"time":53802,"text":"So what we're doing\nis turning our athletes into --"},{"time":58208,"text":"you probably guessed it --"},{"time":60191,"text":"moving dots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61946,"text":"So we've got mountains of moving dots\nand like most raw data,"},{"time":66904,"text":"it's hard to deal with\nand not that interesting."},{"time":69430,"text":"But there are things that, for example,\nbasketball coaches want to know."},{"time":73223,"text":"And the problem is they can't know them\nbecause they'd have to watch every second"},{"time":77057,"text":"of every game, remember it and process it."},{"time":79804,"text":"And a person can't do that,"},{"time":81758,"text":"but a machine can."},{"time":83661,"text":"The problem is a machine can't see\nthe game with the eye of a coach."},{"time":87363,"text":"At least they couldn't until now."},{"time":90228,"text":"So what have we taught the machine to see?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":93569,"text":"So, we started simply."},{"time":95380,"text":"We taught it things like passes,\nshots and rebounds."},{"time":99203,"text":"Things that most casual fans would know."},{"time":101768,"text":"And then we moved on to things\nslightly more complicated."},{"time":104624,"text":"Events like post-ups,\nand pick-and-rolls, and isolations."},{"time":109377,"text":"And if you don't know them, that's okay.\nMost casual players probably do."},{"time":113560,"text":"Now, we've gotten to a point where today,\nthe machine understands complex events"},{"time":118924,"text":"like down screens and wide pins."},{"time":122021,"text":"Basically things only professionals know."},{"time":124771,"text":"So we have taught a machine to see\nwith the eyes of a coach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130009,"text":"So how have we been able to do this?"},{"time":132511,"text":"If I asked a coach to describe\nsomething like a pick-and-roll,"},{"time":135653,"text":"they would give me a description,"},{"time":137317,"text":"and if I encoded that as an algorithm,\nit would be terrible."},{"time":141026,"text":"The pick-and-roll happens to be this dance\nin basketball between four players,"},{"time":145328,"text":"two on offense and two on defense."},{"time":147486,"text":"And here's kind of how it goes."},{"time":149128,"text":"So there's the guy on offense\nwithout the ball"},{"time":151685,"text":"the ball and he goes next to the guy\nguarding the guy with the ball,"},{"time":154918,"text":"and he kind of stays there"},{"time":156199,"text":"and they both move and stuff happens,\nand ta-da, it's a pick-and-roll."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159540,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161779,"text":"So that is also an example\nof a terrible algorithm."},{"time":164913,"text":"So, if the player who's the interferer --\nhe's called the screener --"},{"time":169278,"text":"goes close by, but he doesn't stop,"},{"time":172174,"text":"it's probably not a pick-and-roll."},{"time":174560,"text":"Or if he does stop,\nbut he doesn't stop close enough,"},{"time":178529,"text":"it's probably not a pick-and-roll."},{"time":180642,"text":"Or, if he does go close by\nand he does stop"},{"time":183903,"text":"but they do it under the basket,\nit's probably not a pick-and-roll."},{"time":187462,"text":"Or I could be wrong,\nthey could all be pick-and-rolls."},{"time":190010,"text":"It really depends on the exact timing,\nthe distances, the locations,"},{"time":194602,"text":"and that's what makes it hard."},{"time":196579,"text":"So, luckily, with machine learning,\nwe can go beyond our own ability"},{"time":201547,"text":"to describe the things we know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203314,"text":"So how does this work?\nWell, it's by example."},{"time":205759,"text":"So we go to the machine and say,\n\"Good morning, machine."},{"time":209077,"text":"Here are some pick-and-rolls,\nand here are some things that are not."},{"time":212720,"text":"Please find a way to tell the difference.\""},{"time":215076,"text":"And the key to all of this is to find\nfeatures that enable it to separate."},{"time":218807,"text":"So if I was going\nto teach it the difference"},{"time":220940,"text":"between an apple and orange,"},{"time":222345,"text":"I might say, \"Why don't you\nuse color or shape?\""},{"time":224744,"text":"And the problem that we're solving is,\nwhat are those things?"},{"time":227711,"text":"What are the key features"},{"time":228982,"text":"that let a computer navigate\nthe world of moving dots?"},{"time":232505,"text":"So figuring out all these relationships\nwith relative and absolute location,"},{"time":237352,"text":"distance, timing, velocities --"},{"time":239440,"text":"that's really the key to the science\nof moving dots, or as we like to call it,"},{"time":244392,"text":"spatiotemporal pattern recognition,\nin academic vernacular."},{"time":247925,"text":"Because the first thing is,\nyou have to make it sound hard --"},{"time":250847,"text":"because it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252410,"text":"The key thing is, for NBA coaches,\nit's not that they want to know"},{"time":255575,"text":"whether a pick-and-roll happened or not."},{"time":257521,"text":"It's that they want to know\nhow it happened."},{"time":259621,"text":"And why is it so important to them?\nSo here's a little insight."},{"time":262631,"text":"It turns out in modern basketball,"},{"time":264426,"text":"this pick-and-roll is perhaps\nthe most important play."},{"time":267065,"text":"And knowing how to run it,\nand knowing how to defend it,"},{"time":269709,"text":"is basically a key to winning\nand losing most games."},{"time":272403,"text":"So it turns out that this dance\nhas a great many variations"},{"time":276228,"text":"and identifying the variations\nis really the thing that matters,"},{"time":279900,"text":"and that's why we need this\nto be really, really good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283228,"text":"So, here's an example."},{"time":284428,"text":"There are two offensive\nand two defensive players,"},{"time":286831,"text":"getting ready to do\nthe pick-and-roll dance."},{"time":289007,"text":"So the guy with ball\ncan either take, or he can reject."},{"time":292086,"text":"His teammate can either roll or pop."},{"time":295111,"text":"The guy guarding the ball\ncan either go over or under."},{"time":298121,"text":"His teammate can either show\nor play up to touch, or play soft"},{"time":302710,"text":"and together they can\neither switch or blitz"},{"time":305352,"text":"and I didn't know\nmost of these things when I started"},{"time":308035,"text":"and it would be lovely if everybody moved\naccording to those arrows."},{"time":311979,"text":"It would make our lives a lot easier,\nbut it turns out movement is very messy."},{"time":316047,"text":"People wiggle a lot and getting\nthese variations identified"},{"time":321555,"text":"with very high accuracy,"},{"time":322882,"text":"both in precision and recall, is tough"},{"time":324774,"text":"because that's what it takes to get\na professional coach to believe in you."},{"time":328416,"text":"And despite all the difficulties\nwith the right spatiotemporal features"},{"time":331820,"text":"we have been able to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333318,"text":"Coaches trust our ability of our machine\nto identify these variations."},{"time":337478,"text":"We're at the point where\nalmost every single contender"},{"time":341035,"text":"for an NBA championship this year"},{"time":342682,"text":"is using our software, which is built\non a machine that understands"},{"time":347114,"text":"the moving dots of basketball."},{"time":349872,"text":"So not only that, we have given advice\nthat has changed strategies"},{"time":355049,"text":"that have helped teams win\nvery important games,"},{"time":358425,"text":"and it's very exciting because you have\ncoaches who've been in the league"},{"time":362181,"text":"for 30 years that are willing to take\nadvice from a machine."},{"time":365874,"text":"And it's very exciting,\nit's much more than the pick-and-roll."},{"time":368804,"text":"Our computer started out\nwith simple things"},{"time":370904,"text":"and learned more and more complex things"},{"time":372992,"text":"and now it knows so many things."},{"time":374577,"text":"Frankly, I don't understand\nmuch of what it does,"},{"time":377436,"text":"and while it's not that special\nto be smarter than me,"},{"time":381175,"text":"we were wondering,\ncan a machine know more than a coach?"},{"time":384843,"text":"Can it know more than person could know?"},{"time":386922,"text":"And it turns out the answer is yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388691,"text":"The coaches want players\nto take good shots."},{"time":391272,"text":"So if I'm standing near the basket"},{"time":392947,"text":"and there's nobody near me,\nit's a good shot."},{"time":395137,"text":"If I'm standing far away surrounded\nby defenders, that's generally a bad shot."},{"time":399101,"text":"But we never knew how good \"good\" was,\nor how bad \"bad\" was quantitatively."},{"time":404209,"text":"Until now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405771,"text":"So what we can do, again,\nusing spatiotemporal features,"},{"time":408853,"text":"we looked at every shot."},{"time":410251,"text":"We can see: Where is the shot?\nWhat's the angle to the basket?"},{"time":413280,"text":"Where are the defenders standing?\nWhat are their distances?"},{"time":416066,"text":"What are their angles?"},{"time":417421,"text":"For multiple defenders, we can look\nat how the player's moving"},{"time":420422,"text":"and predict the shot type."},{"time":421879,"text":"We can look at all their velocities\nand we can build a model that predicts"},{"time":425977,"text":"what is the likelihood that this shot\nwould go in under these circumstances?"},{"time":430188,"text":"So why is this important?"},{"time":432102,"text":"We can take something that was shooting,"},{"time":434929,"text":"which was one thing before,\nand turn it into two things:"},{"time":437633,"text":"the quality of the shot\nand the quality of the shooter."},{"time":441680,"text":"So here's a bubble chart,\nbecause what's TED without a bubble chart?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444966,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":446004,"text":"Those are NBA players."},{"time":447339,"text":"The size is the size of the player\nand the color is the position."},{"time":450483,"text":"On the x-axis,\nwe have the shot probability."},{"time":452639,"text":"People on the left take difficult shots,"},{"time":454616,"text":"on the right, they take easy shots."},{"time":457194,"text":"On the [y-axis] is their shooting ability."},{"time":459275,"text":"People who are good are at the top,\nbad at the bottom."},{"time":461861,"text":"So for example, if there was a player"},{"time":463621,"text":"who generally made\n47 percent of their shots,"},{"time":465718,"text":"that's all you knew before."},{"time":467345,"text":"But today, I can tell you that player\ntakes shots that an average NBA player"},{"time":472219,"text":"would make 49 percent of the time,"},{"time":474204,"text":"and they are two percent worse."},{"time":476266,"text":"And the reason that's important\nis that there are lots of 47s out there."},{"time":481714,"text":"And so it's really important to know"},{"time":484287,"text":"if the 47 that you're considering\ngiving 100 million dollars to"},{"time":488267,"text":"is a good shooter who takes bad shots"},{"time":491346,"text":"or a bad shooter who takes good shots."},{"time":495130,"text":"Machine understanding doesn't just change\nhow we look at players,"},{"time":498487,"text":"it changes how we look at the game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500369,"text":"So there was this very exciting game\na couple of years ago, in the NBA finals."},{"time":504148,"text":"Miami was down by three,\nthere was 20 seconds left."},{"time":507379,"text":"They were about to lose the championship."},{"time":509428,"text":"A gentleman named LeBron James\ncame up and he took a three to tie."},{"time":512793,"text":"He missed."},{"time":514015,"text":"His teammate Chris Bosh got a rebound,"},{"time":515876,"text":"passed it to another teammate\nnamed Ray Allen."},{"time":518059,"text":"He sank a three. It went into overtime."},{"time":520002,"text":"They won the game.\nThey won the championship."},{"time":522122,"text":"It was one of the most exciting\ngames in basketball."},{"time":525438,"text":"And our ability to know\nthe shot probability for every player"},{"time":528891,"text":"at every second,"},{"time":530103,"text":"and the likelihood of them getting\na rebound at every second"},{"time":533083,"text":"can illuminate this moment in a way\nthat we never could before."},{"time":537618,"text":"Now unfortunately,\nI can't show you that video."},{"time":540310,"text":"But for you, we recreated that moment"},{"time":544827,"text":"at our weekly basketball game\nabout 3 weeks ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547279,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":549573,"text":"And we recreated the tracking\nthat led to the insights."},{"time":553199,"text":"So, here is us.\nThis is Chinatown in Los Angeles,"},{"time":557478,"text":"a park we play at every week,"},{"time":559066,"text":"and that's us recreating\nthe Ray Allen moment"},{"time":561321,"text":"and all the tracking\nthat's associated with it."},{"time":564772,"text":"So, here's the shot."},{"time":566313,"text":"I'm going to show you that moment"},{"time":568853,"text":"and all the insights of that moment."},{"time":571464,"text":"The only difference is, instead\nof the professional players, it's us,"},{"time":575218,"text":"and instead of a professional\nannouncer, it's me."},{"time":577860,"text":"So, bear with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581153,"text":"Miami."},{"time":582671,"text":"Down three."},{"time":584107,"text":"Twenty seconds left."},{"time":587385,"text":"Jeff brings up the ball."},{"time":590656,"text":"Josh catches, puts up a three!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592631,"text":"[Calculating shot probability]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595278,"text":"[Shot quality]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":597048,"text":"[Rebound probability]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600373,"text":"Won't go!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601570,"text":"[Rebound probability]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603777,"text":"Rebound, Noel."},{"time":605057,"text":"Back to Daria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606509,"text":"[Shot quality]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":610676,"text":"Her three-pointer -- bang!"},{"time":612320,"text":"Tie game with five seconds left."},{"time":614880,"text":"The crowd goes wild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616522,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618205,"text":"That's roughly how it happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619776,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620951,"text":"Roughly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622150,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":624121,"text":"That moment had about a nine percent\nchance of happening in the NBA"},{"time":629629,"text":"and we know that\nand a great many other things."},{"time":631914,"text":"I'm not going to tell you how many times\nit took us to make that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635429,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637200,"text":"Okay, I will! It was four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639096,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":640121,"text":"Way to go, Daria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641647,"text":"But the important thing about that video"},{"time":645934,"text":"and the insights we have for every second\nof every NBA game -- it's not that."},{"time":650639,"text":"It's the fact you don't have to be\na professional team to track movement."},{"time":655083,"text":"You do not have to be a professional\nplayer to get insights about movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658764,"text":"In fact, it doesn't even have to be about\nsports because we're moving everywhere."},{"time":663654,"text":"We're moving in our homes,"},{"time":669428,"text":"in our offices,"},{"time":672238,"text":"as we shop and we travel"},{"time":677318,"text":"throughout our cities"},{"time":680065,"text":"and around our world."},{"time":683270,"text":"What will we know? What will we learn?"},{"time":685589,"text":"Perhaps, instead of identifying\npick-and-rolls,"},{"time":687918,"text":"a machine can identify\nthe moment and let me know"},{"time":690952,"text":"when my daughter takes her first steps."},{"time":693035,"text":"Which could literally be happening\nany second now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696140,"text":"Perhaps we can learn to better use\nour buildings, better plan our cities."},{"time":700362,"text":"I believe that with the development\nof the science of moving dots,"},{"time":704559,"text":"we will move better, we will move smarter,\nwe will move forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708607,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709820,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}